OL,3,CTeenage driver who seriously injured
OL,4,Cboy, 4, in hit-and-run sentenced
OL,6,FThe court was told Doherty had no
OL,7,Fdriving licence, no insurance and that
OL,8,Fone of the car's tyres was critically
OL,9,Funder-inflated.
OL,11,FDoherty, 18, was driving his pregnant
OL,12,Fwife at the time. The court was told
OL,13,Fthey got out of the car, looked at the
OL,14,Fwreckage and saw the boy and his step-
OL,15,Fmother were trapped under the car,
OL,16,Fthen fled the scene.
OL,18,FDoherty's wife returned to get her
OL,19,Fbag. When the boy's trapped step-
OL,20,Fmother pleaded for her to help, she
OL,21,Frefused and ran away again.
