OL,3,CTeenage driver who seriously injured
OL,4,Cboy, 4, in hit-and-run sentenced
OL,6,FThe boy was left trapped under the
OL,7,Fvehicle but Doherty and his wife, who
OL,8,Fwas a passenger in the car, fled the
OL,9,Fscene.
OL,11,FLater that day, Doherty handed himself
OL,12,Fin at a local police station and he
OL,13,Fpleaded guilty to a charge of causing
OL,14,Fserious injury by dangerous driving at
OL,15,FBristol Magistrates' Court.
OL,17,F'My whole world came crashing down' -
OL,18,Fthe boy's father said
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/12
